@startuml sell-events-conceptual
title Sell Stocks — Conceptual: One Business Fact, Many Reactions

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ArrowColor #1f4e79
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #1f4e79
skinparam ComponentBackgroundColor #fff3cd

[PortfolioStockOperationsService\n.sellStock(...)] as core #d4edda
[StockSoldEvent] as evt #e7eef7

[SaleTransactionRecordingListener\n(in-module)] as L1
[AuditTrailListener\n(future)] as L2
[BrokerSyncListener\n(future, out-of-process)] as L3
[BiFeedListener\n(future)] as L4

core --> evt : publish (after FIFO write)
evt --> L1
evt ..> L2
evt ..> L3
evt ..> L4

note right of evt
  The event is the contract.
  Any number of listeners can
  react. The use case never
  needs to know who they are.
end note

note bottom of L1
  Mandatory in this exercise.
  Replaces the synchronous
  transactionPort.save(...) call
  that today lives inside
  sellStock().
end note

note bottom of L3
  Illustrative. In a real
  production system this would
  likely consume an externalized
  version of the same event
  via Kafka.
end note

@enduml
